definition: to gather up/to collect/to edit/to compile

sentences.english: All the letters of the late writer are compiled in this collection.
sentences.chinese: 這個集子輯錄了這位已故作家的所有來往信件。

sentences.english: It was compiled by disciple Wang Hao under my guidance.
sentences.chinese: 這是由弟子王浩在我的指導下所輯錄。

sentences.english: This thesis has compiled all the relevant articles that can be found about Weitian laws at present.
sentences.chinese: 本文輯錄了目前所能見到的有關《爲田律》的文章。

sentences.english: The present Sikong Biaosheng Shiji has been compiled three times by later generations.
sentences.chinese: 現存《司空表聖詩集》，系由後人三次輯錄而成。
